  <prompt>
    Implement the minimum-scope Option Z direction (operator's 2026-05-20 decision):
    SpaarkeAi's Workspace Home tab default content is the Daily Briefing section. Hoist
    Daily Briefing infrastructure (useDailyBriefing + DailyBriefingSection + registration)
    from LegalWorkspace to @spaarke/ui-components so both solutions consume it from the
    shared lib. Update SpaarkeAi's WorkspaceHomeTab to render Daily Briefing as the
    default Home content. Standalone LegalWorkspace continues to render Daily Briefing
    identically. Both web resources redeployed.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React + TypeScript engineer comfortable with monorepo refactors, shared-library
    design, and cross-solution build verification. Familiar with task 034 (Daily Briefing
    creation), task 035 (429 + empty state), task 067 (builder hoist), and the ADR-012
    cross-cutting-component constraint.
  </role>

  <goal>
    @spaarke/ui-components exports useDailyBriefing + DailyBriefingSection + a
    dailyBriefing SectionRegistration. LegalWorkspace's sectionRegistry.ts imports the
    registration from shared lib (instead of solution-local). SpaarkeAi's WorkspaceHomeTab
    renders Daily Briefing as the default Home content (no longer placeholder). Both web
    resources redeployed; standalone LegalWorkspace verified identical; Bug 2 visual is
    materially addressed for the default case.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Operator 2026-05-20 feedback round 1 surfaced Bug 2: SpaarkeAi Workspace pane shows
      structural layout but no actual section content. Task 067 hoisted the canonical
      builder (buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig) to @spaarke/ui-components but left the 6
      section factories solution-local because they each have legal-domain coupling
      (sprk_event, sprk_document, sprk_todo, etc.) — per ADR-012's prohibition on
      hard-coding Dataverse entity names in shared components.

      The operator chose Option Z: SpaarkeAi has a DIFFERENT workspace surface than
      LegalWorkspace. After clarification, the minimum scope is: SpaarkeAi's Home tab
      defaults to Daily Briefing. New workspace tabs are created by user wizards / AI
      outputs (existing mechanism).

      The Daily Briefing factory is the LEAST legal-domain-coupled of the 6:
      - useDailyBriefing.ts calls /api/ai/daily-briefing/narrate via authenticatedFetch
        (shared @spaarke/auth) — no Dataverse entity references
      - DailyBriefingSection.tsx renders Fluent v9 Card + bullets — no domain coupling
      - dailyBriefing.registration.ts is small; passes config to factory

      Task 067's per-factory inventory classified Daily Briefing as "solution-local" but
      the only cited reason was "AI feature stack expansion in shared lib violates
      ADR-013 placement governance." ADR-013 governs BFF placement (server-side), not
      frontend consumption. Multiple solutions consuming the same BFF AI endpoint via
      shared frontend code is NOT an ADR-013 violation. Therefore Daily Briefing is
      safely hoistable to @spaarke/ui-components — revisiting task 067's Option L
      specifically for this section.

      This task closes Bug 2 visually for the default case (Daily Briefing in Home tab).
      Future content (multi-section Home, recent AI sessions, etc.) is deferred to next
      review or follow-on.
    </background>
