  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Daily Briefing infrastructure (hook + section + registration) is consumed by 2+ solutions — it belongs in @spaarke/ui-components. The factory is safe to hoist because it does not hard-code Dataverse entity names (it calls a BFF AI endpoint, which is shared infrastructure).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Daily Briefing extends the BFF in-process; ADR-013 governs server-side AI architecture and is NOT violated by frontend consumers sharing the AI BFF endpoint. Verify the hook calls only existing AI endpoints (no new AI service).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">AI caching — preserve the 5-minute per-user TTL cache from task 034. Verify it works correctly after hoist (cache key uses tenantId from @spaarke/auth getAuthProvider).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-016">AI rate limits — preserve graceful 429 degradation from task 035. The error UI lives in DailyBriefingSection.tsx; verify it works in both solutions.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 tokens only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No accessToken props. Use authenticatedFetch + buildBffApiUrl from @spaarke/auth.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-25 / NFR-10: Standalone LegalWorkspace MUST continue to render Daily Briefing identically. Visual diff = before. The hoist is a refactor not a redesign.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-24: Daily Briefing 429 telemetry. After hoist, ensure telemetry callbacks still fire. The hybrid pattern from task 035 (local trackEvent + optional onRateLimitError prop) should be PRESERVED — verify how it survives the hoist.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Use the re-export shim pattern from task 067 to preserve LegalWorkspace's existing import paths. Files that imported the old path should continue working.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">SpaarkeAi consumes via the public @spaarke/ui-components barrel (no deep imports).</constraint>
  </constraints>

