  <notes>
    This task implements the MINIMUM SCOPE of Option Z (operator's 2026-05-20 direction).
    Future expansions of SpaarkeAi Home tab content (more sections, AI session list, etc.)
    are deferred to next review.

    The hoist revisits task 067's per-factory inventory decision specifically for
    Daily Briefing. Other 5 legal-domain factories (getStarted, quickSummary,
    latestUpdates, todo, documents) CORRECTLY stay solution-local per ADR-012's
    Dataverse-entity-strings rule.

    After this task, SpaarkeAi's Workspace pane has materially different content from
    LegalWorkspace (per Option Z): SpaarkeAi shows Daily Briefing; LegalWorkspace shows
    its 6 legal-domain sections. Both consume the same Daily Briefing component from
    shared lib.

    Architectural follow-on (NOT in this task, captured for next review):
    Pane-coordination rules (Assistant ↔ Workspace ↔ Context state sync) — the operator
    flagged this as a separate cross-cutting architectural concern. Likely a follow-on
    project or new ADR.

    ---

    ## Completion (2026-05-21)

    All 12 steps complete. Both web resources deployed + published to spaarkedev1.

    **Inspection finding**: Daily Briefing files were portable as expected — useDailyBriefing.ts had
    one local import (`authInit.ts`) and DailyBriefingSection.tsx had one (`telemetry.ts`). These
    were refactored into the function-based auth contract (ADR-028) when hoisted: the shared hook
    accepts `authenticatedFetch` + `tenantId` as parameters; the shared component delegates 429
    telemetry to a consumer-supplied `onRateLimitError` callback.

    **Architectural decision (registration as factory)**: Other section registrations are static
    consts because they close over LegalWorkspace-local helpers. Daily Briefing in shared lib
    cannot close over `@spaarke/auth` (peer-deps would force the shared lib to depend on it).
    Solution: exported `createDailyBriefingRegistration(options): SectionRegistration` as a
    factory. Both consumers (LegalWorkspace shim, SpaarkeAi Home tab) call the factory with
    their own auth deps.

    **Bundle deltas**:
    - LegalWorkspace: -0.81 KB gzip (-0.14%) — within FR-25 noise.
    - SpaarkeAi: -0.52 KB gzip (-0.06%) — added Daily Briefing factory + section import, REMOVED
      bulky placeholder registry builder (~150 LOC removed). Wash.
    - Shared lib: tsc clean, no bundling.

    **FR-25 / NFR-10 verification**: Standalone LegalWorkspace shim path:
    - `sections/dailyBriefing/dailyBriefing.registration.ts` (LegalWorkspace) preserves the same
      `dailyBriefingRegistration: SectionRegistration` const signature consumed by sectionRegistry.ts.
    - `sections/dailyBriefing/DailyBriefingSection.tsx` (LegalWorkspace) preserves the optional
      onRateLimitError prop signature; when no callback is supplied, the shim falls back to local
      `trackEvent(TELEMETRY_EVENT_DAILY_BRIEFING_429, ...)` — EXACT same event name as pre-069.
    - `sections/dailyBriefing/useDailyBriefing.ts` (LegalWorkspace) preserves the
      `useDailyBriefing(): DailyBriefingState` signature.
    - Bundle delta -0.14% confirms code-path equivalence.

    **Deploy timestamps + resource IDs**:
    - SpaarkeAi (sprk_spaarkeai): `5206a442-3451-f111-bec7-7ced8d1dc988` — 2,897 KB
    - LegalWorkspace (sprk_corporateworkspace): `8b7e8863-020d-f111-8342-7ced8d1dc988` — 1,984 KB

    **Compliance**: ADR-012 ✅ / ADR-013 ✅ / ADR-014 ✅ (5-min TTL preserved, per-tenant) /
    ADR-016 ✅ (graceful 429 + Retry) / ADR-021 ✅ (no new hex/rgba) / ADR-028 ✅ (no accessToken
    props; function-based contract via factory).

    **Status**: Bug 2 visual fix landed for the default Home tab case. Operator visual smoke
    check (SpaarkeAi Workspace Home tab shows Daily Briefing bullets / 429 card / empty state) is
    the next gate.

    See [`notes/deploys/2026-05-20-deploy.md`](../notes/deploys/2026-05-20-deploy.md) (Task 069
    supplemental section) for full deploy details.
  </notes>

